{
  "texts": [
    "As a result, we successfully completed 206 out of the 250 simulations across the 46 polymers.",
    "Details on the simulations that failed due to configurational instability and were incomplete due to the missing forcefield parameters are included in the supporting information.",
    "Fig. 4b presents the distribution of ionic conductivity and transference number of the top 46 candidates among the 100K generated candidates.",
    "As indicated in the figure, the ionic conductivities of these promising candidates are significantly higher than those in the existing training dataset.",
    "Notably, 17 of the 46 candidates surpass the highest conductivity polymer (conductivity = 5.07 × 10-4 S/cm) in the training set (Fig. 4c)."
  ]
}